  "commentary": "With SPX at 6872.32 sitting just below the massive +16B gamma wall at 6875, dealers are aggressively selling into this rally as they hedge their long gamma positions, creating immediate resistance. The PIN regime with 77.9B total GEX suggests strong mean-reverting forces, while the recent gex_surge event indicates fresh option flows are amplifying the stabilizing effect around current levels. Key inflection points are 6875 resistance (dealers sell) and 6846 GEX flip below - any break under the flip would shift dealers to short gamma and accelerate downside momentum toward the 6700 support level.\n\nBottom line: expect selling pressure to cap upside near 6875 with choppy action in the 6846-6875 range.",
